-- U.K. Chancellor Nominates Chakrabarti for EBRD Head, Times Says
-- B y   G a v i n   F i n c h
-- 2012-03-17T11:15:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-17/u-k-chancellor-nominates-chakrabarti-for-ebrd-head-times-says.html
U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer
 George Osborne  has nominated Suma Chakrabarti to be the new head
of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, going
against a convention that the job goes to a non-British
candidate, the Times of London reported.  Chakrabarti is currently the permanent secretary of the
Ministry of Justice, the Times said. France proposed Philippe de Fontaine Vive Curtaz, vice president at the  European Investment
Bank , and Poland put forward former Prime Minister Jan Krzysztof Bielecki as its candidate, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gavin Finch in London at 
 gfinch@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
 eevans3@bloomberg.net  